Common.Strapline.Common.Text: DA APPROVED SITE IN THRIVING NEWTOWN

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as exclusive agents are pleased to bring 20-28 Munni Street, Newtown to the market For Sale by Expressions Of Interest closing Wednesday 30 September 2020 at 4pm.

This property offers a purchaser a prime development opportunity within one of the most highly regarded neighbourhood in Sydney’s Inner West. The property is well serviced by public transport and is provided direct access to the CBD and surrounding suburbs as it is in walking distance of Newtown Station, Erskineville Station and St Peters Station.

Features of the property include:
•	Opportunity to lodge new DA for five torrens title terraces to increase yield (S.T.C.A.)
•	Existing DA approval by award winning architect, Smart Design Studio 
•	Regular and flat topography with 23m* street frontage
•	Site has been demolished and ready to build
•	R1 General Residential
•	North facing block
•	Located 4km south west of Sydney CBD
•	600m* to Newtown Station
•	Adaptable zoning with many uses

To reiterate, this property is offered For Sale via expressions of interest closing on Wednesday 30 September 2020 at 4pm.

For further information please contact the exclusive sales agents.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: A RARE 971SQM* DEVELOPMENT OPPORTUNITY IN THE VIBRANT SUBURB OF NEWTOWN

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Iconic retail tenant, The Italian Bowl

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 255 King Street, Newtown. This three-storey freehold building comprises two residential units and 50% of the ground floor retail shop, tenanted by the multi-award winning restaurant, The Italian Bowl. Situated in the heart of Newtown along the bustling King Street and leased to one of the suburb’s most iconic eateries, the property is a secure investment in Sydney’s rapidly growing Inner West.

255 King Street, Newtown benefits from the following key attributes: 

-	Two double storey residential units plus 50% of the ground floor retail shop
-	Tenanted by The Italian Bowl, winner of multiple awards including ‘Best Restaurant in the Inner West’ in the Inner West Local Business Awards 
-	NLA: 259sqm* 
-	Land area: 133sqm* 
-	Estimated market net income: $179,637 per annum 
-	Secure investment with refurbishment upside
-	B2 Local Centre zoning 
-	Set to benefit from the future Lennox Street car park upgrade 
- Burgeoning suburb with strong scope for growth
- Deceased Estate

255 King Street, Newtown will be offered for sale via public auction on Tuesday, 4 December 2018 at 10.30am.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate
